      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0000180">
               <p><persName>Elizabeth (née Molland)</persName> was <persName>Ebenezer
                     Blackwell</persName>&apos;s first wife, and a close friend of <persName>Hannah
                     Dewell</persName>. From <date when="1749">1749</date> the
                     <persName>Blackwells</persName> shared ownership and lived with
                     <persName>Dewell</persName> in the <placeName>Limes, Lewisham</placeName>. The
                  three of them were close friends and supporters of both <persName>CW</persName>
                  and <persName>JW</persName>. When <persName>Elizabeth</persName> died on <date
                     when="1772-03-27">Mar. 27, 1772</date>, <persName>CW</persName> composed an
                  extended funeral hymn (MS Death of <persName>Elizabeth Blackwell</persName>). See
                  Martin, <hi rend="italic">Grasshopper</hi>, 49–69.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
